post_text:
On a normal day, our educators are tasked to teach.

But in times of adversity, we are reminded that teaching is not the only thing our educators are charged with doing. They are also our surrogate parents, protectors, friends, mentors and heroes.

These pledges/promises they made for the new school year tell us that our educators are more than willing and able to go above and beyond their duty to teach. Their courage in facing the unknown is what makes them a Teacher. It is what makes them special.

Thank you for your strength and your enduring care for our students while also looking out for your own self and family.

If you have to put someone on a pedestal, put Teachers. They are society’s heroes.

post_text:
In an effort to help STOP the spread of COVID-19, iLearn Schools is constantly exploring and investing in new technologies. We are pleased to inform you that iLearn Schools has partnered with MyMealtime.com, a convenient and secure online service for monitoring your student’s lunch account and making credit or debit card deposits as needed. iLearn Schools will use this online service for other school payments as well. School fees such as aftercare and extended day programs fees and field trips, yearbooks, etc. will be collected only through this online platform.
There is no service charge attached to this service. We strongly encourage all of our parents to use this “FREE” and convenient platform to send money for your child (ren).
Please note that if your child is participating in the aftercare program, you must make the payment via mymealtime.com. Schools will no longer accept cash/check at campuses.
Any other school fees over the $20 threshold will only be collected via mymealtime.com.

School administration will provide additional guidance when necessary.

post_text:
Our very own Ms. Melissa Marash is featured on NJDOE Virtual Professional Learning. Her video on “Creating Digital Choice Boards in Google Slides” can be watched on YouTube: https://youtu.be/wQdS1SJTRWk
Choice boards are a great way to engage all learners and provide students with an opportunity to practice new material in many different ways. During this 30-minute session, Ms. Marash addresses five tips for a high-quality digital activity. She then models how to create a choice board in Google Slides showing some specific technology techniques to create your own unique digital worksheet. Last we will discuss ways to make this activity accessible and differentiated for all learners.
Way to go Ms. Marash!

Hello Passaic Panthers!

Passaic Elementary Arts and Science Charter School holds an annual Art Show every April. Unfortunately, this year we can’t all be together like usual, so we will have a virtual Art Show instead!

Art Show Link: https://youtu.be/67YI7z0gzL4

Students were asked to create anything they wanted and submit their work from home. This video is a collection of all the artwork that was submitted. Some of our teachers even created artwork of their own!

Please feel free to share the link with family and friends.

Thank you to everyone who participated.
I hope you enjoy the show!

-Ms. Blodgett

If you would like to skip ahead to your grade,
here are the starting times for each section.

Kindergarten: 0.40
1st Grade: 2:52
2nd Grade: 4:52
3rd Grade: 6:54
Teachers: 8:46

This is the fourth consecutive year that Bergen Arts & Science Charter High School has been recognized as one of New Jersey's top 50 High Schools according to the newly released U.S. News and World Report.
In addition to being ranked 47th in the state, Bergen Arts and Science Charter High School is also ranked 1,077th across the entire nation and earned a silver medal. Schools are ranked based on their performance on state-mandated tests, as well as on how well they are able to prepare students for college.
Overall Score 93.95/100

post_text:
Continue Learning - Distance Learning Can Be Real Learning

With so many students learning from home, the critical question we face as educators today is: what does effective and productive distance learning look like exactly? Through distance learning, schools can continue making great strides forward with students for the future. In fact, with the right infrastructure and learning management systems in place, along with hotspots to allow all students Internet access from home, distance learning can still result in real learning. Without these systems already in place, continuing education at the same rate as before would be virtually impossible. Many schools across the country are struggling to provide the resources necessary for students to continuously be challenged in meaningful and measurable ways from home.

Always striving to stay a step ahead and prepared for any hurdles thrown its way, iLearn Schools was thankfully ahead of the curve and prepared for such a challenge.

#iContinueLearning

post_text:
With everything that is going on around COVID-19, it is understandable that some of us may feel confused, anxious, stressed or alone. It’s normal to feel these things but know that there are ways we can combat this.
At iLearn Schools, we believe that emotional and mental well-being is as important as our physical well-being, that is why we are bringing you #iCare!

#iCare is an informational tool that will offer our iLearn Schools community resources to support you at this challenging and unprecedented time. We will bring you inspirational messages, how-to’s, information and measures we can take care of ourselves and our families.
At iLearn Schools, we believe that no matter the challenge in front of us, we can conquer it together through our caring and continued commitment to learning and growing in the face of adversity.

Remember, we are all in this together and we salute each and everyone of you for doing such an amazing job!

Yours,
iLearn Schools Community

Introducing iLearn Schools' Digital School Enrolment System (iEnroll)

We are pleased to announce our new digital school enrollment system (iEnroll). Parents can now complete their child's enrollment electronically. To iLearn Schools 2020 admission lottery winners, please expect to receive an email from your schools, and please follow the steps in the attached video in order to complete your enrollment.
Parents, please be advised that you are given seven days to complete your enrollment, and all required supporting documents will be collected upon return to school, and before the end of the academic year.
#iContinueLearning
text:
Introducing iLearn Schools' Digital School Enrolment System (iEnroll)

We are pleased to announce our new digital school enrollment system (iEnroll). Parents can now complete their child's enrollment electronically. To iLearn Schools 2020 admission lottery winners, please expect to receive an email from your schools, and please follow the steps in the attached video in order to complete your enrollment.
Parents, please be advised that you are given seven days to complete your enrollment, and all required supporting documents will be collected upon return to school, and before the end of the academic year.
#iContinueLearning

iLearn Donates Goggles to St. Barnabas Hospital
St. Barnabas Hospital, in the Bronx, is fighting desperately against the uptick in COVID-19, and eye protection is an essential piece in keeping their health professionals safe. iLearn Schools donates goggles to St. Barnabas Hospital as they are dealing with a severe shortage of medical supplies.
iLearn is here to help you! #COVID19

Dear iLearn Schools Families:

Please note that although our schools are closed in an effort to slow the spread of coronavirus, iLearn Schools’ front offices will still remain open for parents to CALL, DURING REGULAR SCHOOL HOURS. Parents, be aware that you can CALL your school’s campus during distance learning. Our school administrators, school secretaries, school nurses, school counselors, school psychologists, and all support personnel will all be available to answer your questions. Simply dial your school's phone number, and we will be happy to assist you during this time.
#icontinuelearning

Announcement:
For the safety of our school communities and in an effort to slow the spread of COVID-19, all school-wide events across iLearn Schools are cancelled for the next 2 weeks through Wednesday, March 25th with the exception of iLearn Academy and the iStellar program. School plays and all parent-involved activities, including parent-teacher conferences, are cancelled during this 2-week period. Unless our school's athletic conference cancels competition, our sports practices and games will however still take place.

Thank you for your attention to this important matter, and may everyone stay healthy and safe.

post_text: In preparation for the possibility of distance learning occurring in response to COVID-19, iLearn Schools is conducting a Professional Development with all staff and will have an early dismissal for students on Friday, March 13, 2020. In addition, all schools will be closed on Monday, March 16, 2020 for a full day staff PD. Schools will resume their regular full day schedule on Tuesday, March 17, 2020. Thank you for your cooperation in this matter, and know that our first priority is always to ensure the continued health and safety of our students, staff and families.

post_text:
INTENT TO RETURN FORM!
Dear iLearn Parents/Guardians:
As part of the iLearn Schools' admission policy, all enrolled students are eligible for re-enrollment the following year, until they graduate from the school. For consideration of automatic re-enrollment, all parents are required to complete the Intent to Return Form every year.
Intent to Return Forms will give us a better understanding of those families who wish to continue enrollment for their children at any of our charter schools. This form must be completed for each child that is currently enrolled.
Introducing iLearn "e-sign" Portal!
A new feature has been created for parents/guardians to read and sign school-wide policies and updates more conveniently. Parents can now complete their intent to return forms at “e-Sign” portal.

Dear Parent(s)/Guardian(s);

We want to inform you that 2020-2021 kindergarten sibling(s)’ registration is now open. Please note that cutoff date requirement for kindergarten students to attend the Passaic-ASCS is October 31st. Your sibling(s) must be 5 years old before or on October 31st, 2020.

As outlined in N.J.S.A. 18A:36A-8, Passaic-ASCS’s admission policy requires that siblings of students enrolled have the opportunity for an early enrollment and they receive preference for acceptance into the school. The admission policy also requires that kindergarten sibling(s) must complete all required enrollment documents prior to the lottery date. If you have an eligible sibling(s), you can report to the Passaic-ASCS front office and complete the registration process. Completion of the kindergarten sibling(s) enrollment documents is due Friday, February 28th. If a parent misses the deadline, sibling(s) will be required to enter the lottery.

Thank you for your interest in Passaic-ASCS.

January 27, 2020 marks 75 years since the liberation of Auschwitz-Birkenau, the largest concentration camp established by the Nazis. It is estimated that at minimum 1.3 million people were deported to Auschwitz between 1940 and 1945; of these, at least 1.1 million were murdered. To remember all the victims, along with the millions of other victims of the Holocaust, and encourage the prevention of future genocides, the United Nations designated this day each year as International Holocaust Remembrance Day.

This solemn occasion reminds each of us to pause and reflect on the importance of collective action against antisemitism and other forms of bias to ensure respect for the dignity and human rights of all people everywhere.

#WeRemember

Dear iLearn Schools Community,

Amid a rise in hate crimes around the country, including the recent attack in Jersey City, it is more important than ever we work to ensure all of our schools and all of our students are safe.

Unfortunately, NJDOE's proposed rules for school security funding for all public schools inexplicably excludes public charter schools. This means that public charter schools are singled out as the only schools in New Jersey being denied access to critical security funding grants. We need to collectively TAKE ACTION in order to get this fixed.

We need YOUR HELP to get NJDOE to reverse this position and give public charter schools access to the funding that they deserve!

CLICK THE LINK IN THE COMMENT SECTION BELOW to send an email to the Governor's Office, Department of Education, Legislative Leadership and your local legislators so that our students are protected.

Thank you for taking the time to do this for your children!

Sincerely,
iLearn Schools

𝗖𝗼𝗻𝗴𝗿𝗮𝘁𝘂𝗹𝗮𝘁𝗶𝗼𝗻𝘀 𝘁𝗼 𝗼𝘂𝗿 𝗶𝗦𝗧𝗘𝗟𝗟𝗔𝗥 𝗦𝘁𝘂𝗱𝗲𝗻𝘁 𝗼𝗻 𝘁𝗵𝗲 𝗔𝗠𝗖 𝟴® 𝗛𝗢𝗡𝗢𝗥 𝗥𝗢𝗟𝗟

iStellar student Yessica J. (8th Grade, BASCS) made it to the Honor Roll on AMC 8® 2019, scoring TOP 5% nationally among 94,645 contestants.

𝗡𝗼𝘁𝗮𝗯𝗹𝗲 𝗰𝗼𝗺𝗽𝗲𝘁𝗶𝘁𝗶𝗼𝗻 𝗽𝗲𝗿𝗳𝗼𝗿𝗺𝗮𝗻𝗰𝗲𝘀 by iStellar students Pardhav C. (8th grade, HASCS) and Trashgim M. (7th grade, PASCS) who won first place in their respective schools.

American Mathematics Competition (AMC 8®) is the first of a series of competitions in secondary school mathematics that determine the United States team for the International Mathematical Olympiad (IMO). Organized by the Mathematical Association of America since 1985, AMC 8® is the most widely participated mathematics competition for grades 8 and below in the US.

Be Grateful 5K was a Huge Success!

What better way for families to celebrate Thanksgiving in the morning than to run together!
iLearn Schools Thanksgiving Run presented by Fair Lawn Chamber of Commerce, celebrated all things we are thankful for 2019. The event was open to runners of all ages, abilities, and welcomed runners, walkers, dogs, strollers, wagons, turkey hats, turkey costumes, and more.
Proceeds from this event will go toward enhancing the academic and enrichment programs for all our iLearn Schools students.

post_text:
In Remembrance of a War Hero and Friend - A Life that Beams Light into Tomorrow 🇺🇸 When our schools reached out to a veteran in our community many years ago to speak with our students on Veteran’s day, we did not know then that this veteran and friend would become such a major part of who we are still today. At approximately 10 p.m. on October 31st of 2019, Vito “Pal” Trause passed away at the age of 94.

If anyone sees another new star shining bright in the night sky, know that it's Trause beaming light and hope for the future. Any donations that can be made to the Wounded Warrior Project would be greatly appreciated in celebrating the life of an old pal who continues to make a difference.

post_text:
Congratulations!

iLearn Math Contest at Princeton University has been a great success again this year. Over 200 students from 24 middle schools across New Jersey competed for various prizes. The event aims to promote interest and enthusiasm for mathematics among secondary school students. Students are expected to work on challenging and fun mathematics problems along with hands-on tasks on different rounds of the contest.
A special compliments to the Bergen ASCS Middle School Math Team and coach Mr. Joseph Kantrowitz for winning the first place team award.

Farewell dinner for our special guests from Italy!

Congratulations to all students and their families! Students of our Bergen High School Campus took part in an Italy Exchange Trip by partner-shipping with a High School (Liceo Elsa Morante) in Naples. Students were hosted by families in both countries. The program was designed to facilitate and develop a genuine and mutually beneficial exchange process for teaching, research and outreach activities between both High Schools.

post_text:
A New Chapter in iLearn Schools' History!

Due to the notable increase in iLearn staffing volume, for the first time, the iLearn Summer Institute was hosted at an outside location, Montclair State University Campus. Additionally, Bronx ASCS's staff were greeted by NJ coworkers, and for the first time in iLearn history, educators from two different states had worked together and learned from each other. Congratulations to all faculty and staff!

iLearn Academy Summer Program was a huge success!

iLearn Academy supports the creation of community learning centers that provide academic enrichment opportunities during non-school hours and summer. The program is open only for iLearn Middle Schools 4th through 8th grades students. 19-20 registration information will be announced soon. Stay tuned...
